<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/834</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to my cable of January 11, 4 p.m. Negotiations for private
                            settlement, resumed Saturday, resulted in agreement on tariff and
                            various matters connected with railway administration. Other questions
                            postponed until return of Mr. Norton who leaves for United States
                            to-morrow. Situation encouraging.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>